-- GE Capital Hires Matthews From Barclays for Europe Leveraged-Finance Unit
-- Karen Eeuwens
-- 2010-06-28T16:18:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/ge-capital-hires-matthews-from-barclays-for-europe-leveraged-finance-unit.html

          
          
             GE Capital, the finance arm of
 General Electric Co. , appointed Dan Matthews as an executive
director in its European leveraged finance unit.  
 Matthews will be based in London, reporting to Paul Scott,
managing director and head of sponsor coverage, the company said
in a statement. He joins from Barclays Plcâ€™s strategic debt
finance division, where he spent five years structuring private-
equity backed deals in the U.K.  
 Matthews previously spent six years at N.M. Rothschild &
Sons Ltd., originating senior and mezzanine deals.  
